tables.table_schema:
CREATE TABLE charging_history (
   charging_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
   vehicle_id INT,
   charging_date DATE,
   charging_start_time TIME,
   charging_end_time TIME,
   charging_duration INTERVAL,
   charging_cost DECIMAL
);

CREATE TABLE charging_history (
  event_id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
  charging_station_id UUID,
  vehicle_id UUID,
  start_time TIMESTAMP,
  end_time TIMESTAMP,
  kwh_delivered FLOAT
);

CREATE TABLE charging_stations (
    id INT,
    station_name VARCHAR(50),
    location VARCHAR(100),
    PRIMARY KEY (id)
)

CREATE TABLE vehicle_profiles (
    vehicle_id INT,
    model_name VARCHAR(50),
    battery_capacity DECIMAL(10,2),
    PRIMARY KEY (vehicle_id)
)

CREATE TABLE charging_records (
    record_id INT,
    vehicle_id INT,
    station_id INT,
    charging_start DATETIME,
    charging_end DATETIME,
    energy_delivered DECIMAL(10,2),
    PRIMARY KEY (record_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (vehicle_id) REFERENCES vehicle_profiles(vehicle_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (station_id) REFERENCES charging_stations(id)
)

CREATE TABLE vehicles (
    id INT,
    vehicle_name VARCHAR(255),
    charging_status VARCHAR(50),
    charge_start_time TIMESTAMP,
    charge_end_time TIMESTAMP
);

CREATE TABLE charging_stations (
    station_id INT,
    station_name VARCHAR(255),
    location VARCHAR(255),
    operator VARCHAR(100),
    price_per_kwh DECIMAL(10,2)
);

CREATE TABLE charging_sessions (
    session_id INT,
    vehicle_id INT,
    station_id INT,
    start_time TIMESTAMP,
    end_time TIMESTAMP,
    kwh_delivered DECIMAL(10,2)
);

CREATE TABLE users (
    user_id INT,
    username VARCHAR(100),
    email VARCHAR(255),
    registration_date DATE,
    last_login TIMESTAMP
);

CREATE TABLE Charging_Records (
    record_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    vehicle_id INT,
    station_id INT,
    start_time TIMESTAMP,
    end_time TIMESTAMP
);
